    \section{On Gurren Lagann}
episode 3, 

kamina and simon as partners
we were shown that simon really understands kamina - how kamina wasn't really searching for his dad, or misses him, but how he regretted the opportunity to keep on going. 
themes, rather than manliness, it's the idea of keep moving forward. rising over obstacles. 
I'm not quite sure what yoko stands for. 
another moment is when simon was like "I'm scared, but I'm sure we can win tomorrow, and kamina was like "that's the part I think will save my life one day." 
Where are the dreams? GL is more about rising over obstacles, overcoming first yourself, others, and then the world (fate)? 
the more I think about it, CP couldn't be anymore different than GL. 
whereas CP is about never truly succeeding? 


ep 4
that was so messed up 
they joked about boota being emergency rations, but when boota himself offered to be emergency rations, that was a bit too much. 
I'm not really quite sure what the simon-kamina interactions here meant. 
in this episode, we were introduced to the dark something siblings. the three girls and one dude. it took a long time for kamina to accept simon's combination. kamina kept swatting simon away. I wonder what I can say about kamina, as kamina was in a position where he was being pressured to combine as well, as well as the one saying no to simon. Simon was confused as ever. 


